The paper deals with rigidity and rank-robustness functions of matrices, which are concepts commonly studied in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of elimination theory of polynomial ideals suggests a connection to algebraic geometry (cs.AG) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions applications in circuit complexity and communication complexity, which could place it in the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or systems and control (cs.SY).
